{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# S3 — Gerrit project + LLM-Review label + submit requirement + submitWholeTopic\n\n## Why\nThis is the gate's integrity rule: a change is submittable ONLY when the deterministic\n`LLM-Review` vote is MAX and there are no unresolved comments. `copyCondition` avoids re-paying\nfor an expensive LLM review on a no-code-change re-upload; `submitWholeTopic` lands whole\nreviewed features atomically. The integrity property is not just \"the label gates submit\" but\n\"ONLY the bot can set the label\" — so a human cannot cast `LLM-Review` and bypass the gate.\nGerrit is pinned to **3.14.1** (d251 docker-compose), so every predicate/feature used here\n(`-has:unresolved`, `copyCondition`, submit requirements) is above its minimum and was\nvalidated to parse against live 3.14.1.\n\n## What\n- Create the `rebar` project in Gerrit (NoteDb).\n- `LLM-Review` label in `refs/meta/config` (project.config): `function=NoBlock`; values `-1..+1`;\n  **`copyCondition = changekind:NO_CODE_CHANGE`** (peer-pattern correction). We deliberately do\n  NOT include `changekind:TRIVIAL_REBASE`: a TRIVIAL_REBASE copies the vote even when the change\n  was rebased onto a **different base** (diff is byte-identical but the base moved), which would\n  certify a tree the LLM never reviewed against the new base — the \"copyCondition certifies an\n  unreviewed tree\" risk the Opus red-team flagged. `NO_CODE_CHANGE` pins the parent tree, so it\n  only carries the vote across a true no-op re-upload (e.g. commit-message-only edit). A real\n  rebase therefore drops the vote and forces a fresh review (the safe default for a correctness\n  gate). `function=NoBlock` is **required, not a free choice**: on 3.14.1 a blocking label\n  function is rejected, so blocking comes from the submit requirement.\n- Submit requirement (project.config): `submittableIf = label:LLM-Review=MAX AND -has:unresolved`.\n  This is what blocks submit; the label is advisory on its own. Both predicates validated to\n  parse (HTTP 200) on live Gerrit 3.14.1.\n- `change.submitWholeTopic=true` — set in the **server-level** `gerrit.config` `[change]`\n  section, NOT in project.config (it is a server-global key, silently ignored in project.config).\n  GOTCHA (peer research): topics are **global + un-namespaced**, so a topic name reused in a repo\n  the submitter can't see could silently block submit; for this single-repo PoC that risk is\n  minimal, but adopt a topic naming convention (e.g. `rebar-<feature>`) and document it.\n- Access controls: grant the auto-generated `label-LLM-Review` vote permission to the **Service\n  Users** group; humans may push changes for review but cannot submit without the label and\n  cannot themselves cast `LLM-Review`. The Service Users group is created/wired in **S4**; S3\n  lands config that references it and is testable in S3 by an **admin** casting the vote.\n\n## Scope\nIn: project + `LLM-Review` label (NO_CODE_CHANGE copyCondition) + submit requirement +\nserver-level topic config + the label ACL grant. The \"only the bot votes\" end-to-end proof is\ncompleted in S4 (the bot account does not exist in S3); in S3 the vote is exercised by an admin.\nOut: the bot account + event/vote wiring (S4); replication (S5); GitHub lockdown (S6). Gerrit\nversion is fixed upstream by d251 (3.14.1).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/gerrit/project.config` (pushed to `refs/meta/config`): label, submit requirement,\n  `copyCondition=changekind:NO_CODE_CHANGE`, ACL grant.\n- `infra/gerrit/gerrit.config` (server-level): `[change]\\n  submitWholeTopic = true`. (Impl\n  note: same gerrit.config d251 mounts; S3 owns/patches the `[change]` section.)\n- `infra/gerrit/setup-project.sh`: provisions the project + pushes `refs/meta/config`. Impl\n  notes (not separate ACs): (a) **idempotent** — push a fully-declarative project.config via\n  `git push HEAD:refs/meta/config`, guard project creation with check-before-create; (b)\n  **auth** — needs Gerrit admin creds (HTTP password / SSH key), source documented (env/SSM),\n  fail-fast if absent; (c) **dry-run/diff** mode before mutating the live instance.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A change can be pushed for review to the `rebar` project; submit is BLOCKED until\n      `LLM-Review=+1` (MAX) AND no unresolved comments — verified by an admin casting the vote\n      (the bot-only path is proven in S4). Both predicates parse + enforce on 3.14.1.\n- [ ] The `label-LLM-Review` vote permission is granted **exclusively** to the Service Users\n      group: a regular developer cannot cast `LLM-Review` (push `%l=LLM-Review+1` is rejected /\n      not applied) while a Service-Users member can.\n- [ ] `copyCondition=changekind:NO_CODE_CHANGE` carries the vote across a no-code-change\n      re-upload (e.g. commit-message-only amend) BUT a genuine rebase onto a moved base\n      (TRIVIAL_REBASE) does NOT carry it — the vote is dropped and re-review is required.\n      Verified on 3.14.1 by (a) a message-only amend keeping the vote and (b) a real rebase\n      dropping it.\n- [ ] `change.submitWholeTopic=true` is set in server-level `gerrit.config` `[change]` (NOT\n      project.config), and demonstrated: two changes under one topic submit atomically and\n      neither submits independently while its topic partner is open.\n- [ ] The submit requirement is the SINGLE code-review vote in v1 (no human Code-Review / CI\n      Verified yet — follow-on epic 1fa8). Record this deliberate single-gate stance + planned\n      evolution in a brief ADR/note."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782699631537444001,"uuid":"b4133f5d-0de6-414c-aedf-6917d896016c"}